        <h2> The beginning in New Zealand </h2>
        <p> So the plan is to fly at the beginning of October, around October 8th, from Hamburg via London and Singapore towards Auckland, New Zealand. The travel time will be almost 2 days, plus the time shift from then +11 hours. Once there, a rented camper van should be waiting for me the next day at the latest. I would like to get the car directly on the same day so that I can jump in directly. Off, make the next beach and make me undisturbed. I assume that after the long flights I will be quite flat and annoyed. <!--more-->
        </p><p> The next day I will meet Sam because she gets the order for us to get SIM cards so that we can coordinate when and where we want to meet. Furthermore, of course, to send GPS data and Twitter/blog posts via mail here and there. </p>
        <p> In the next 14 days it should be quite casual with the motorhomes across both islands. So in between we have to translate the ferry from the north to the south island. </p>
        <p> The goal of my 14 -day trip will then be Christchurch, which should be one of the largest cities on the South Island. Sam will present her camper van Reise for another 26 days. In turn, I will give back my car in Christchurch and maybe explore Christchurch on foot for another day or 2 before going to Australia. </p>
