        <h2> Scenario 1: I get 3 months of vacation </h2>
        <p> This scenario is quite simple and short because I have not really assumed my vacation for months. In this case, I will either fly to the west coast in the north of the east coast in the north of the east coast or to Perth. Buy or rent a camper van there and drive back to Sydney. Always stop when I feel like it or it's worth it. Just enjoy the beauty of nature and the coast. What about work? Well we will see that on site. Which is the case for backpackers. In any case, I would like to go to a training farm. With or without a subsequent job on a real farm. New Year's Eve should then be celebrated in Sydney; With huge fireworks and such. From there back to Ireland, it should go over Hamburg again. Visiting your loved ones and hopefully showing a lot of tan and many experiences. </p>

        <h2> Scenario 2: I have to give up my job </h2>
        <p> Here the topic is already more complex. So before I even break towards Oceania, I break off all tents here in Ireland and bring all my things to Germany to my warehouse. At the beginning of October as described above to New Zealand. At the end of October I would fly from Christchurch to Sydney. </p>
        <p> Once there, first to see that I get my papers sorted and find a job in my job. According to relevant websites, these are quite well sown and paid just as well. (Hope that the data is correct). Of course I will try to find a good job on site from home. With this job I would stay in Sydney until New Year's Eve to look at the huge fireworks. </p>
