        <p> In January I would like to go to Melbourne by bus from Sydney. The bus tickets costs approximately $ 100 (approx. 85 &euro;) for the total of almost 1000km and the travel time is approximately 12 hours. On the way there, a stopover in Canberra is planned for a day or two with a cultural program. </p>
        <p> In Melbourne I might want to stay for about one to two weeks and visit the cliffs 'twelve apostles' from there and look at the wild penguins. But I think that a full 2 &#8203;&#8203;weeks could be too long for me. </p>
        <p> It is planned to fly from Melbourne to Perth and to stay there for a few days. After all, Perth is said to be one of the most beautiful cities in Australia. It is planned to buy a camper van there. After a few final security checks, this starts towards Adelaide. A total of over 2,500km. </p>
        <p> Most of it on Highway 1 along the south coast. On the way there I would like to watch some of the many hopefully beautiful wineries and whiskey distilling and, if possible, would also be happy to work there. </p>
        <p> Adelaide is also a stage destination on my piece of paper, as there should be pandas in the Zoo there. If necessary, I would try to find a job in my job again and stay there for a few weeks. If the camper van has aroused enough trust in me and find one or two passengers, it should then go from the outback through the outback via Alice Springs (Ulluru) to Cairns. I have already selected alternative route along the east coast via Sydney and Brisbane for Cairns. But I hope that I can drive through the desert to the rainforest. </p>
